    "client_msg_id": "2a2dc187-ebfd-4e5e-9c7a-5f7ac05b02df",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Certainly; I think the way Prolog by default throws away information from searches across queries (modulo certain ways of tabling) is tragic. Much if not all of the intelligence of a search-based programming system is in which search paths to take of course.\nInteraction with the environment is related but in the way I'm developing things that topic isn't directly addressed by the search strategy but rather by making goals that represent those interactions and propagate the information from them to the rest of the system.",
